# Richtato Agent Context

Richtato is an AI-native personal finance app and Monarch Money competitor. The product should feel polished, data-forward, fast, responsive, and trustworthy across dark and light mode.

## Source Of Truth

- Start with `AGENTS.md` for agent orientation and current pitfalls.
- Frontend patterns live in `frontend/CLAUDE.md`.
- Backend patterns live in `backend/CLAUDE.md`.
- API details live in `API_REFERENCE.md`; verify live endpoints against Swagger at `/api/docs/` when the backend is running.
- Cursor rules live in `.cursor/rules/` and should stay focused, scoped, and low-duplication.

## Current Stack

- Backend: Django 5.x, Django REST Framework, PostgreSQL, Gunicorn, Loguru, Plaid, OpenAI.
- Frontend: React 19, TypeScript, Vite 6, React Router 7, Tailwind CSS 3.4, Shadcn/Radix, ECharts, TanStack Table, Sonner.
- Infrastructure: Docker Compose for local development; production serves the frontend through Django/Nginx-style container flow.

## Architecture Defaults

- Backend: Views validate HTTP, services own business logic, repositories own ORM queries.
- Frontend: Pages compose feature components, components call `lib/api/*` service singletons, contexts hold global state.
- Follow existing local patterns before adding abstractions. Keep changes scoped and avoid unrelated refactors.

## Current Routes And APIs

- Frontend routes use `/dashboard`, `/transactions`, `/accounts`, `/budget`, `/setup`, `/preferences`, `/household`, `/formulas`, `/profile`, `/upload`, and `/more`.
- `/cashflow` redirects to `/dashboard`; `/settings` redirects to `/preferences`.
- API base is `/api/v1/`; budgets are under `/api/v1/budgets/`; auth, profile, preferences, and category settings are under `/api/v1/auth/`.
- Household APIs are under `/api/v1/household/`; household-aware reads use `scope=household` only when the household scope is selected.

## Coding Standards

- Use CSS variables and Tailwind tokens; do not hard-code colors in new UI.
- Use Lucide icons, Sonner toasts, project format helpers, and `cn()` for conditional classes.
- Use `loguru.logger` in backend code and avoid new frontend `console.log`.
- Mutating frontend API calls should use CSRF-aware helpers.
- Run the relevant checks from `.cursor/rules/pre-commit-checks.mdc` before committing.
